body:
@vicdeo thanks for the info.
i have thought that the type of database could influence the result, but i have done the upgrade with sqlite and mysql and the result is the same.
before performing the upgrade, i have set the log to debug level. after upgrade, owncloud.log contains:

	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368636606}
	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368636615}
	{"app": "core", "message": "starting upgrade from 4.90.9 to 5.0.8", "level": 2, "time": 1368636616}
	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368636616}
	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368636617}
	....

the trace "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database." is repeated indefinitely.

in the case of correct upgrade from 4.5.8 to 5.0.6 rc1, owncloud.log file contains:

	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368639231}
	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368639234}
	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368639234}
	{"app": "files", "message": "starting app upgrade from 1.1.6 to 1.1.7", "level": 0, "time": 1368639234}
	{"app": "core", "message": "starting upgrade from 4.90.9 to 5.0.7", "level": 2, "time": 1368639237}
	{"app": "files_versions", "message": "starting app upgrade from 1.0.2 to 1.0.3", "level": 0, "time": 1368639249}
	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368639250}
	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368639251}
	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368639251}
	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368639251}
	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368639251}
	{"app": "files_pdfviewer", "message": "starting app upgrade from 0.1 to 0.2", "level": 0, "time": 1368639253}
	{"app": "contacts", "message": "starting app upgrade from 0.2.4 to 0.2.5", "level": 0, "time": 1368639253}
	{"app": "gallery", "message": "starting app upgrade from 0.5.1 to 0.5.2", "level": 0, "time": 1368639256}
	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368639256}
	{"app": "core", "message": "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", "level": 0, "time": 1368639259}
	...

and although keeps repeating the trace "adding user backend instance of oc_user_database.", the browser displays a message indicating that the upgrade was successful and allows the login on the new version of owncloud.
